Asked whether Mr Cameron felt that Suarez had set a ‘bad example’ to young children, the spokesman replied: ‘I think the implication is fairly clear.’

The footballer, who is married to his childhood sweetheart Sofia Balbi and has a two-year-old daughter, will not face police action after Ivanovic said he did not want to press charges.

