Last night, Nicola Cooper, headteacher at the bitten boy’s school, Golftyn Primary, declined to speak about the incident. No one was available to comment at Flintshire County Council.

Professional Footballers’ Association chief executive Gordon Taylor said Suarez would be offered anger management counselling.

He said: ‘There is no doubting his football ability, that’s why it is so disappointing and embarrassing when he lets himself down.

‘We have to work hard on anger management now. We have trained counsellors in this field and we will be offering their services to Liverpool and the player to try to improve matters.’

